GAME DESIGN DOCUMENT - INDIE HORROR GAME

TITLE: Haaira's Castle

GENRE: First-Person Psychological Horror / Survival

TARGET AUDIENCE: Adults 16+

CORE CONCEPT:
Explore an abandoned castle, collect cursed dolls, and escape from a supernatural threat.

GAMEPLAY PILLARS:
1. Exploration - Navigate complex castle environment
2. Resource Management - Limited stamina and battery
3. Evasion - Avoid/outsmart pursuing enemy
4. Progression - Burning dolls increases tension
5. Atmosphere - Immersive sound design and lighting

PLAYER MOTIVATIONS:
- Curiosity (what is the castle? why the dolls?)
- Survival instinct (escape Haaira)
- Story completion (what happens in the ending?)

TARGET PLAYTIME: 30-60 minutes (first run)

CORE MECHANICS:
1. Movement (Walk, Sprint with stamina, Crouch)
2. Flashlight (Limited battery, directional light)
3. Interaction (Collect items, read notes, burn dolls)
4. Pursuit (Avoid enemy, hide/escape)

PROGRESSION:
Phase 1 (0-20 min): Building tension, doll collection
Phase 2 (20-45 min): Escalating danger, enemy transformation
Phase 3 (45-60 min): Climax, final escape sequence

DIFFICULTY SCALING:
- Fixed difficulty (no settings to avoid frustration balancing)
- Haaira becomes faster after 6 dolls burned
- More frequent appearances as story progresses
- Limited resources create tension

ACCESSIBILITY:
- Subtitles for all dialogue/audio cues
- Adjustable flashlight brightness
- Color-blind friendly UI
- Option to reduce motion effects (screen shake)

SUCCESS CONDITIONS:
- Burn all 7 dolls
- Escape castle with Haaira

FAILURE CONDITIONS:
- Caught by Haaira
- Out of battery with no escape route
- Stuck in unintended geometry (rare, level design prevents)

STORY THEMES:
- Isolation and vulnerability
- The unknown (ambiguous ending)
- Psychological horror (tension over gore)
- Redemption or damnation (open interpretation)

EMOTIONAL JOURNEY:
Start: Fear, curiosity
Middle: Dread, urgency
End: Relief, confusion, existential uncertainty

TARGET PLATFORMS:
- PC (Windows, Linux)
- Consoles (optional: Switch, PS5, Xbox)
